Final Answer:

Here are 3 nut-free recipes each for lunch and dinner, along with their ingredients and recipe links:

Lunch Recipes:

1. DIY Pizza Lunchable
Ingredients: Mini bagel or English muffin, pizza sauce, pepperoni, shredded mozzarella cheese
Recipe: https://amindfullmom.com/peanut-free-lunches/

2. Turkey Club Roll-Up
Ingredients: Deli turkey, lettuce, cheese, avocado, bacon, tortilla wrap
Recipe: https://amindfullmom.com/peanut-free-lunches/

3. Veggie Burrito
Ingredients: Mushrooms, beans, corn, avocado, tortilla wrap
Recipe: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/collection/nut-free-recipes

Dinner Recipes:

1. Chicken Puttanesca
Ingredients: Chicken, garlic, tomatoes, olives, capers, olive oil
Recipe: https://dairyeggandnutfree.com/category/recipes/dinner/

2. Irish Beef Stew
Ingredients: Beef, potatoes, carrots, celery, onions, beef broth
Recipe: https://dairyeggandnutfree.com/category/recipes/dinner/

3. One-pot Vegan Rice and Beans
Ingredients: Rice, kidney beans, green olives, peppers, vegetable broth
Recipe: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/collection/nut-free-recipes

All these recipes are nut-free and suitable for someone with a nut allergy. Remember to always check the ingredients of any packaged items you use to ensure they are nut-free.

